# Translate to English on "stop"

When the user sends a message that consists only of `stop` (case-insensitive, ignoring surrounding whitespace and punctuation), treat it as a request to translate the most recent non-English text or draft in the active context into English.

- Do not interpret `stop` as a request to halt the conversation when there is translatable text available.
- Return only the English translation unless the user asks for explanation or alternatives.
- Preserve meaning, tone, formatting, names, links, and code blocks.
- If there is no clear text to translate, ask which text should be translated to English.
